cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language change and uses natural language processing techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised model for detecting metaphoric change. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses information-theoretic measures to detect semantic change. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of entropy to detect changes in word usage over time. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the societal impact of language change and proposes a new test set for annotation.
